=== Gastroparesis and Delayed Gastric Emptying
<subsec:gastroparesis>

*Clinical Presentation.*

    - Feeling full after small amounts of food
    - Persistent nausea
    - Vomiting (especially of undigested food)
    - Abdominal bloating and discomfort
    - Unpredictable blood sugar fluctuations

*Mechanism.*
Gastroparesis reflects autonomic dysfunction affecting the vagus nerve, which controls gastric motility. Impaired stomach emptying creates digestive symptoms and nutritional challenges.
